    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Describes the style and culture of the Mangarevans. Few works of art created by the Mangaveran survive today due to their destruction by orders of missionaries in the 19th century. The few surviving sculptures and fragments demonstrate that the Mangareva figures are of a rectangular frame. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000045262/Grove Dictionary of Art online (1999-2002)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Describe obras creadas por los Mangareva. Pocas obras creadas por los Mangareva sobreviven hoy en día debido a la destrucción ordenada por los misionarios del siglo XIX. Las pocas esculturas y fragmentos demuestrn que las figuras Mangareva presentan un armazón rectangular.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Beschrijft werken die zijn vervaardigd door het Mangareva-volk. Er zijn nog maar weinig Mangareva-kunstwerken bewaard gebleven, aangezien de meeste in de 19de eeuw op last van missionarissen zijn vernietigd. De weinige nog resterende beeldhouwwerken en fragmenten laten zien dat de Mangareva-figuren rechthoekige contouren hadden.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052383/Winkler Prins Atlas (1987)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>描述由曼加瑞瓦居民所創作的作品。曼加瑞瓦人所創作的藝術品，由於西元十九世紀時傳教士下令將之摧毀，因此僅有少數留存至今。少數留存至今的雕像與藝術作品之碎片，足以顯示曼加瑞瓦的人像採長方形的骨架外型。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
